definition.value: a blood albumin level abnormal AE with an outcome of a decrease in the amount of albumin, a protein made by the liver

label.value: blood alkaline phosphatase level abnormal AE

definition.value: a liver related investigation result abnormal AE that has an outcome of an abnormal level of alkaline phosphatase in the blood
a blood alkaline phosphatase abnormal AE that has an outcome of a decreased level of alkaline phosphatase in the blood

a blood alkaline phosphatase abnormal AE that has an outcome of elevated levels of alkaline phosphatase, an enzyme responsible for removing phosphate groups. a liver/biliary system AE that has an outcome of an increased amount of ALP, an isoenzyme that removes phosphate groups commonly found in the bile ducts but also found in the bone

a distal neuropathy AE which shows a neurological disorder characterized by progressive weakness and impaired sensory function in the legs and arms. It is caused by the loss of myelin sheath of the peripheral nerves.
a blood amylase level abnormal AE that has an outcome of an increased amount of amylase, an enzyme that helps digest carbohydrates; may indicate disease or inflammation of the pancreas
a liver related investigation result abnormal AE that has an outcome of an abnormal amount of bilirubin in the blood
a blood bilirubin level abnormal AE with an outcome of a increased amount of bilirubin, or a yellow breakdown product  (broken down hemoglobin) of normal heme catabolism, in the blood
a physical quality that has a decreased amount of calcium in the bloodstream
A physical quality that has an decreased level of chloride ion in the blood, excessive loss may be due to sweating, vomiting and adrenal gland/kidney disease
a blood cholesterol abnormal AE with the result of an increase in cholesterol level in the blood

label.value: blood creatine phosphokinase level abnormal AE

definition.value: an enzyme investigation result abnormal AE that has an outcome of abnormal levels of creatine phosphokinase in the blood
a blood creatinine level abnormal AE that has an outcome of an increased level of creatinine in the blood (due to lack of kidney activity)
an infection adverse event that has an outcome of bacteria or yeasts in the blood

a hematopoietic system AE that has an outcome of disease in the blood, a living tissue made up of plasma and red blood cells, white blood cells and platelets. Blood disorders affect one or more parts of the blood and prevent the blood from doing this job.
a blood folate abnormal AE that has an outcome of a decreased level of folate in the blood
a blood glucose level abnormal AE that has an outcome of a decrease of glucose levels in blood
a blood glucose level abnormal AE that has an outcome of an increased glucose level in blood
a blood homocysteine level abnormal AE that has an outcome of an increased levels of homocysteine in the blood

label.value: blood immunoglobulin A level increased AE

definition.value: an immunology and allergy investigation result abnormal AE that results in an increased immunoglobulin a level in the blood

label.value: blood lactate dehydrogenase level increased AE

definition.value: a blood lactate dehydrogenase level abnormal AE that has an outcome of an increased amount of LDH, an enzyme that could indicate tissue damage
A physical quality that has an decreased level of magnesium, a mineral involved in nerve signaling and bone health. Deficiency can cause spasms, and muscular cramps.
a blood parathyroid hormone level abnormal AE that has an outcome of a decrease in the level of parathyroid hormone in the blood
A physical quality that has an decreased level of decreased phosphorus in the blood
a physical quality where the blood potassium level is decreased.
a hypotension AE that has an outcome of a decrease in the amount of pressure in the arteries when the heart is at rest between beats
a hypotension AE that has an outcome of immeasurable blood pressure
A physical quality that has an decreased level of sodium concentration in the blood
a blood thromboplastin level abnormal AE that has an outcome of an increase in the level of thromboplastin in the blood
a blood urea level abnormal AE with an outcome of a decreased amount of urea nitrogen in the blood, below 7 to 21 mg of urea per 100 ml
a blood urea level abnormal AE that results in an increase in amount of urea in blood

label.value: blood uric acid level increased AE

definition.value: a blood uric acid level abnormal AE that has an outcome of an increase in uric acid in the blood; excess purines may accumulate in tissues and form crystals
a bone disorder AE that has an outcome of a cyst that forms on the bone
a bone disorder AE that has an outcome of surgery to clean and flush out the infected bone
a bone disorder AE that has an outcome of an anomlay in the growth or structure of a bone
a bone marrow disorder AE that has an outcome of an abnormal condition in which the bone marrow is unable to produce normal amounts of red blood cells, white blood cells and platelets

Bone marrow produces three types of blood cells; red blood cells, white blood cells and platelets. Bone marrow depression is characterized by an inability or reduced ability of the bone marrow to produce these cells. A low blood count can involve just one or all three types of blood cells.

a hematopoietic system AE that has an outcome of disease in the bone marrow, the spongy tissue inside of some bones that contain stem cells that can develop into red blood cells, white blood cells or platelets

a bone marrow disorder AE that has an outcome of an insufficient amount of red blood cells, white blood cells or platelets, associated with fanconii anemia, dyskeratosis congenita, and aplastic anemia
a bone marrow disorder AE that has an outcome of an excess formation of connective tissue in the bone marrow
a bone marrow disorder AE that has an outcome of the decrease in cells responsible for providing immunity, carrying oxygen and blood clotting
a bone marrow disorder AE that has an outcome of the replacement of damaged bone marrow with healthy bone marrow stem cells
a swelling AE that results in swelling around a bone
a skin adverse event that has an outcome of an early stage of squamous cell carcinoma
a bradycardia AE that results in a decreased heart rate in a neonate
an edema AE that has an outcome of edema or swelling of the extravascular compartment from uptake of water in the gray and white matter
a tumor AE that has an outcome of cancer in the breast
a breast cancer AE that has an outcome of cancerous cells spreading to the breast
a breast cancer AE that has an outcome of breast cancer at the stage III level
an infection AE that results in the breast becoming infected
a pain AE that results in pain in the breast
